[[File:Frederika Menezes, author from Goa, India.jpg|thumb|Frederika Menezes, borovpi, koviitri ani kolakar.]]Frederika Menezes ek [[Goenkar]] [[borovpi]], [[koviitri]] ani [[kolakar]] asa. Tika tichea, "Unforgotten" pustoka khati vollkhotat. Tichea, ''The Different Normals'' kovita, Goenchea Xikxonn Mondollachea Inglix Ikravea vorga khatir patthiopustokant  aspav zala.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/36081344.cms |title=Life lessons from a personal story of always seeing the bright side |work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.heraldgoa.in/Goa/Goa-Board-to-introduce-new-subject-in-psychology/109380.html |title=Goa Board to introduce new subject in psychology |work=Herald Goa}}</ref>

Frederika don dotoranchim dhuv asa ani ti [[Ponnje]] [[Altinho]] vaddlea. Mendu sombondit ar tika asun, ti opangull loganchea prosnachi kodd ghevpi zavn asa.<ref name="Observer2017>{{cite news |url=https://www.goanobserver.in/2017/04/01/frederika-menezes-shows-way/ |title=Frederika Menezes shows the way! |work=Goan Observer}}</ref>

Frederika-chea her vavrant ''The Portrait'' (kovitenchi punji ji 1998 vorsa uzvaddavpant aili), "The Pepperns and Wars of the Mind" (ek 2003 vorsantli vismitachi kanni) ani "Stories in Rhyme" (ek kovnachem pustok bhurgeam khatir jem 2014 vorsam porgottpant ailem); aspavtat.<ref name="Observer2017 /> Ti ek  voir sorpi kolakarui zavn asa. Aplem rongovop onkio rupant, eka tablet, smartphone vo PC hancher korta fokot ek bott vaprun ti. korta.<ref name="Triumphs2018" />

2016 vorsa, tika Sahitient Yuva Srujan Puraskar divpant aila.<ref name="Triumphs2018">{{cite web |url=http://goastreets.com/the-triumphs-of-frederika-menezes/ |title=The Triumphs of Frederika Menezes |work=Goa Streets}}</ref>  Bharotachea adle Raxttrpoti sorgest Dr. Abdul Kalam hannem tichea poilea pustokachi tokhnnai kelea., Tachea huzram tika tichea kovitenchea pustokantlem vachop Goenchea Vidhan Sobhent korpak lailam..<ref>{{cite news |url=http://goastreets.com/frederika-menezes/ |title=Frederika Menezes  - Triumph of A Literary Spirit |work=Goa Streets}}</ref>

